body.p:
But all this is styled with the same color, blue in our case. It is impossible using standard
      CSS to style just the chapter number with a larger font, and with red. However, you can do it
      using multiple befores:

body.codeblock:
h1:before(3) {
  content: "Chapter ";
  color: blue;
}
h1:before(2) {
  content: counter(chapter);
  color: red;
  font-size: large;
}
h1:before(1) {
  content: ".";
  color: blue;
}
